The paper discusses privacy-preserving authentication, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY). The paper also presents a new protocol for privacy-preserving set intersection, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of implicit authentication for risk mitigation, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
